President Obama has declared a major disaster in North Dakota due to a severe winter storm that occurred between April 29 and May 1, 2011. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The affected counties include Bottineau, Burke, Divide, Dunn, McKenzie, Mountrail, Renville, Ward, and Williams. Federal funding is available for emergency work, facility repair or replacement, and hazard mitigation measures. Willie G. Nunn has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.